goals.question: What is the distribution of cities in terms of latitude?

code:
```
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    state_counts = data.groupby('state').count()['city']
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(12, 6))
    ax.bar(state_counts.index, state_counts.values, color='blue')
    ax.set_xlabel('State')
    ax.set_ylabel('Count of Cities')
    ax.set_title('What is the distribution of cities across different states?')
    plt.xticks(rotation=90)
    plt.tight_layout()
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.scatter(data['lon'], data['lat'], s=10, alpha=0.5)
    plt.xlabel('Longitude')
    plt.ylabel('Latitude')
    plt.title('What is the geographical distribution of cities in the dataset?')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data.copy()
    data.dropna(subset=['city'], inplace=True)
    city_counts = data['city'].value_counts()
    top_city = city_counts.index[0]
    top_city_count = city_counts.iloc[0]
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    ax.bar(city_counts.index, city_counts.values, color='blue')
    ax.axhline(top_city_count, color='red', linestyle='--', label=f'Top city count: {top_city_count:.2f}')
    ax.set_xlabel('City')
    ax.set_ylabel('Count')
    ax.set_title('What is the most common city in the dataset?')
    ax.legend()
    plt.xticks(rotation=90)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.hist(data['lon'], bins=20, color='green')
    plt.axvline(data['lon'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label='Mean')
    plt.xlabel('Longitude')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.legend()
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.hist(data['lat'], bins=20, color='green')
    plt.axvline(data['lat'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Mean: {data['lat'].mean():0.2f}")
    plt.xlabel('Latitude')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.legend(loc='best')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
